<subSubSection pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="82.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,836,861]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Terayama" authorityYear="2009" box="[324,452,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yuhuang">
<emphasis box="[324,338,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[355,452,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">yuhuang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a single specimen, for which the external morphology cannot be clearly observed. We redescribed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Terayama" authorityYear="2009" box="[526,649,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yuhuang">
<emphasis box="[526,540,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[553,649,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">yuhuang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the 
<typeStatus box="[801,899,871,896]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">holotype</typeStatus>
and additional specimens. Although 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Terayama" authorityYear="2009" box="[1312,1436,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yuhuang">
<emphasis box="[1312,1326,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1340,1436,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">yuhuang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Terayama" authorityYear="2009" box="[376,539,908,933]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiyangshen">
<emphasis box="[376,390,909,932]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[404,539,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">taiyangshen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differences in the antennal segment ratios and the form of the subpetiolar teeth can demonstrate that they are separated species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
